description:
src/persona.rs:95-122 — persona::update issues up to 4 separate SQL UPDATE statements, one per non-None field:

    if let Some(name) = display_name {
        sqlx::query("UPDATE personas SET display_name = ? WHERE username = ?")...
    }
    if let Some(bio_text) = bio {
        sqlx::query("UPDATE personas SET bio = ? WHERE username = ?")...
    }
    // ... avatar, header

Each is an independent database round-trip. A single dynamically-built UPDATE query (e.g., using a SET clause builder) would be more efficient and atomic — currently if the third UPDATE fails, the first two have already committed.

Impact: Non-atomic updates — partial writes are possible on error. Also 4x database round trips where 1 would suffice.
